HEADWORD: Disseizor
<hw>Dis*sei"zor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Law)</fld>
<def>One who wrongfully disseizes, or puts another out of possession of
a freehold.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>disseisor</asp>.]</altsp>
<rj><au>Blackstone.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

